
Python script to recursively unrar split archives in many directories, and then delete the rar files.

e.g.

Archive 1/
    archive1.r00
    archive1.r01
    archive1.rar
    SubFolder/
        subarchive.r00
        subarchive.r01
        subarchive.r02
        subarchive.rar
Archive 2/
    archive2.part1.rar
    archive2.part2.rar
    archive2.part3.rar

Should unrar the files and delete the rar files.
Use at your own risk, It could unrar incorrectly and then delete all your files.

I accept no responsibility for loss of data.

